When you activate the network, you do it in a way that information 
propagates from one neuron to the next. Basically, you go through each 
neuron, and take all of its inputs and compute its output. Then proceed 
to the next until you have computed the output for every one of them. 
And that is one &quot;activation&quot; step. In order to ensure information will 
flow through the entire network so it reaches all output neurons, you&#39;d 
do this activation a bunch of times. In cases where loops exist, do the 
activation just once, or a fixed number of times. These networks don&#39;t 
really settle and stabilize on one single output pattern, they work 
continuously.

